The paper focuses on the security risks of mobile banking apps, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also proposes an automated security risk assessment system, which involves program analysis techniques and keyword identification, indicating a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and system identification (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the global distribution of banking apps and their weaknesses, which could fall under the categories of cybercrime (cs.CY) and programming languages (cs.PL) as the weaknesses are related to data-related vulnerabilities in the apps.
